ELSEWHERE



➤ STATE WATCH



Texas has a water problem. As The Hill’s Saul Elbein writes, the Lone Star State is finally paying attention to the threats that extreme drought and flooding pose to the state’s long-term water supply. It is one aspect of the danger that weather — strengthened by a warming climate — poses to Texas and to native Texans. “We are already the most vulnerable state in the country to these extreme weather disasters,” climate scientist Katherine Hayhoe told The Hill. “And then we have climate change loading the dice against us.”&nbsp;



